Revision history for PDL-EEG

0.03   2026-07-18
  BREAKING
    - .LOG events now carry data-sample positions ({samp}/{t_data}). extblock
      placement corrected: the .LOG elapsed-seconds clock also counts paused
      time between recording blocks, so anchoring events to it drifted them by
      tens to hundreds of seconds and misfiled late segments (some clamped to
      the data end). Events are now placed by REC START-delimited segments
      against exact block boundaries; task-marker positions in multi-segment
      files change (and are now correct). Re-epoch any saved event positions.
  ADDED
    - clock_to_samp() maps wall-clock to samples through block_meta (piecewise,
      break-aware); nk_to_mul.pl --cut-clock is now correct across recording
      breaks (was a naive wall==data map that leaked the next block into a cut).
    - wfmblock: .LOG events are placed for concatenated multi-block reads
      (all_blocks); previously wfmblock events had no sample position at all.
    - xt/70_real_data.t: real-data event-placement regression (extblock +
      wfmblock; REC STARTs land exactly on block boundaries).
  FIXED
    - lib/PDL/EEG.pm: malformed $VERSION line (the module did not compile;
      `use PDL::EEG` died). Also refreshed the module list (EDF is implemented).

0.02   2026-07-17
  BREAKING
    - extblock multi-segment read; DC returned in µV (was 1000x low);
      gap_samples default 0; DC numbering by format signature (unknown croaks).
  ADDED
    - mul_to_nk.pl --solve-bne; {units}/{n_samp_per_block}/{block_meta};
      read_mul; per-signal EDF dimension; t/13; mk_synthetic_nk --long.

0.01  2026-06-12
    - Initial release
    - PDL::EEG::IO::NihonKohden: read Nihon Kohden EEG-1100C binary files
      - Confirmed format from real hardware (EEG-1100C, JE-921A amplifier)
      - Waveform data: uint16 offset binary, 0.09765625 µV/bit
      - Sampling rate auto-detected from wfmblock header (+0x1A lower 14 bits)
      - Channel labels from .21E file (CRLF-aware) with DEFAULT_LABELS fallback
      - BCD timestamp decode (YY/MM/DD HH:MM:SS)
      - Event parsing from .LOG file (ASCII 6-digit seconds format)
      - n_samples computed from inter-block gap
      - Multi-block support (block => N option)
    - examples/verify_read.pl: step-by-step verification tool
    - examples/read_nihonkohden.pl: interactive viewer with giza_server sliders
      - Horizontal slider: time axis scroll
      - Vertical slider: gain (µV/div)
      - Decimation for render performance (step_max=5)
